channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: It's 2020 All Over Again. Google Bans Trump Ad Targeting Black Voters
Biden warns Netanyahu against Rafah invasion as Israel prepares for action
item.description: President Biden called Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu over the phone on Monday, warning the prime minister against continuing with plans for an invasion of the Gaza city of Rafah.

item.title: Heritage Foundation: Biden Admin Colluded With Dem Groups to Sway Vote
item.description: A new report by the Heritage Foundation's Oversight Project indicates Biden administration officials worked with Democratic Party-aligned groups to craft and implement a seemingly neutrally worded executive order for the practical effect of activating traditionally...

item.title: Power Grab: Biden Admin Tries to Control National Guard, Texas Gov. Greg Abbott Claps Back
Group of conservative judges vows to not hire Columbia University law students due to anti-Israel protests
item.description: A group of conservative federal judges sent a letter to Columbia President Minouche Shafik, vowing to not hire graduates because of the school's response to anti-Israel protests.

item.title: Japan Tells US That Biden's 'Xenophobia' Comment Is Regrettable
item.description: Japan has described as "regrettable" President Joe Biden's comment that "xenophobia" is stifling the Asian nation's economic growth, the top government spokesperson said Tuesday.

item.title: NY v Trump to resume after former president threatened with jail, told trial to last at least 2 more weeks
item.description: The unprecedented criminal trial of former President Trump resumes Tuesday morning after the 2024 presumptive Republican presidential nominee was again held in contempt of court.

item.title: Rob Schmitt Investigates: Secret Billionaires' Leftist Crusade
item.description: In a Newsmax special presentation, "Rob Schmitt Tonight" turned the spotlight on the network of billionaires and their radical-left causes that are funding everything from the anti-Israel protests on college campuses to making sure Donald Trump never sees a second term.

item.title: WATCH: Pro-Hamas Freaks Win Hearts and Minds By Vandalizing a WWI Memorial and Burning an American Flag
GOP committee chair demands answers from DC officials on controversial noncitizen voting law
item.description: The head of the House Administration Committee is expressing concern about what he sees as D.C. officials encouraging non-citizen voting in upcoming elections.

item.title: Democrat Rep. Tim Kennedy Sworn In, Narrowing GOP Majority
item.description: Rep. Tim Kennedy, D-N.Y., took his oath on the House floor Monday, succeeding retired Rep. Brian Higgins, D-N.Y., tipping the balance of power with the GOP holding just a one-vote margin on any partisan vote, The Hill reported.

item.title: This Endorsement of Fani Willis May Just Be the Funniest Ever
'Squad' member caught at fundraiser hosted by Islamic leader who praised Hamas attack on Israel
item.description: New York Rep. Jamaal Bowman, a member of the far-left "Squad," was caught attending a fundraiser co-hosted by an Islamic leader who said he was "happy" about the Oct. 7 Hamas attack.

item.title: Biden to Condemn Antisemitism in Speech Amid Gaza Protests
item.description: President Joe Biden will speak out against antisemitism at a Holocaust memorial ceremony Tuesday, as tensions remain high over nationwide campus protests against Israel's war in Gaza.
